\begin{frontmatter}

\title{Topographical Orthogenetic Generative Theory in Strong Interactions\\
       \large Contact Geometry, dm$^3$ Operator Cycle, and Fold Events in Nuclear Matter}

\author[label1]{Pablo Nogueira Grossi}
\address[label1]{G6 LLC, Newark, New Jersey, USA}
\ead{pablogrossi@hotmail.com}

\begin{abstract}
We apply the Topographical Orthogenetic Generative Theory (TOGT) to strong-interaction physics. The contact 3-manifold structure with Reeb flow and curvature plane $\ker\alpha$ supplies a geometric backbone for the non-Abelian dynamics of quarks and gluons. The dm$^3$ operator cycle ($C \to K \to F \to U$, closed by entropic boundary $E$) generates the orthogenetic recurrence whose dominant eigenvalue is the Tribonacci constant $\eta \approx 1.839$. The geometric weight $\eta^{-k}$ induces a fractal measure $\mu_\eta$ on the contact distribution.

At nuclear scales this framework describes hadronization and quark-gluon plasma evolution as iterated fold events in an effective contact geometry. Macroscopic analogs (black-hole singularities and converging fluid waves) illustrate the same $C \to K \to F$ sequence. The $g=33$ stability threshold emerges naturally as a lock-in scale for coherent structures. All operator algebra is verified in the AXLE engine (Lean 4). Explicit falsifiability conditions are stated for lattice QCD, heavy-ion collision spectra, and analogue gravity experiments.
\end{abstract}

\begin{keyword}
TOGT \sep contact geometry \sep strong interactions \sep quark-gluon plasma \sep fold events \sep analogue gravity
\end{keyword}

\end{frontmatter}

\section{Introduction}
Quantum Chromodynamics (QCD) is the established theory of the strong interaction \citep{altarelli2017qcd,gross1973asymptotically,politzer1973reliable}. At short distances asymptotic freedom permits perturbative calculations, while at nuclear scales non-perturbative phenomena---confinement, hadronization, and collective behavior in quark-gluon plasma (QGP)---require geometric insight beyond conventional field-theoretic methods \citep{beane2010nuclear,savage2012nuclear}.

TOGT provides a contact-geometric formulation in which the strong-interaction vacuum or nuclear medium is modeled as a 3-manifold $(M^3,\alpha)$ equipped with a Reeb vector field $R_\alpha$ (orthogenetic time) and a maximally non-integrable distribution $\ker\alpha$ (curvature plane). The generative mechanism is the composite operator
\[
G = U \circ F \circ K \circ C,
\]
acting along the Reeb flow and producing the orthogenetic recurrence
\[
w(k+3) = w(k+2) + w(k+1) + w(k).
\]
The characteristic root $\eta \approx 1.839$ (plastic number) defines the universal scaling, with geometric weight $\eta^{-k}$ yielding the TOGT fractal measure $\mu_\eta$.

This paper shows that nuclear and hadronic phenomena arise as iterated applications of the dm$^3$ cycle, with fold events ($F$) corresponding to confinement or singularity-like transitions. The framework is grounded in lattice QCD results for nuclear matter \citep{beane2010nuclear,deForcrand2010nuclear} and analogue-gravity models of wave singularities \citep{barcelo2011analogue,braunstein2024analogue}.

\section{Contact 3-Manifold Formulation of Strong Interactions}

Consider an effective contact form $\alpha$ on a 3-manifold describing the local geometry of the QCD vacuum or nuclear medium. The Reeb vector field satisfies
\[
\alpha(R_\alpha) = 1, \qquad \iota_{R_\alpha} d\alpha = 0.
\]
The curvature plane $\ker\alpha$ hosts the non-Abelian degrees of freedom (color-charged excitations). Because $\ker\alpha$ is maximally non-integrable, trajectories under the Reeb flow cannot remain planar and must accumulate curvature until a Whitney-type fold occurs.

The operator cycle is defined as:
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Compression ($C$)}: Infall or density increase (gravitational or color confinement analog).
\item \textbf{Curvature ($K$)}: Twisting of flow lines in $\ker\alpha$, generating shear analogous to gluon self-interaction.
\item \textbf{Fold ($F$)}: Geometric singularity where smooth projection fails---interpreted as hadron formation or effective singularity in dense nuclear matter.
\item \textbf{Unfolding ($U$)}: Relaxation and reconfiguration, restoring coherence for the next cycle.
\item \textbf{Entropy ($E$)}: Boundary condition (dissipation, horizon-like causal isolation) enforcing stability at threshold $g=33$.
\end{itemize}

The composite $G$ propagates along $R_\alpha$, inducing the Tribonacci recurrence and the weighted measure $\mu_\eta$.

